<h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>48% of queries trigger AI Overviews</strong> as of March 2026. Up 58% year over year.</li>
<li><strong>Organic CTR drops 34-61%</strong> when an AI Overview appears. Every major study confirms this.</li>
<li><strong>60% of searches end without a click.</strong> Zero-click is the new default for most informational queries.</li>
<li><strong>Only 38% of cited pages rank in the top 10.</strong> AI Overviews pull from a much wider source pool than organic results.</li>
<li><strong>Brands cited in AI Overviews earn 35% more clicks.</strong> Being cited is the new ranking. <a href="/blog/optimize-google-ai-overviews/">Optimize for AI search visibility</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Healthcare (88%), Education (83%), and B2B Tech (82%)</strong> face the highest AI Overview rates by industry.</li>
<li><strong>Content freshness matters 3x more</strong> for maintaining AI citations. Update quarterly at minimum.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Methodology</h2>
<p><strong>Sources:</strong> Ahrefs, Semrush, Seer Interactive, Search Engine Land, SparkToro, Advanced Web Ranking, Digital Applied, ALM Corp, The Digital Bloom, DemandSage, SE Ranking, Amsive Digital.</p>
<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> April 2026</p>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> We update this page quarterly to ensure all statistics remain current. When a stat changes from a prior version, we note the updated date. Measurement methodologies vary between studies. Where sources report different numbers for the same metric, we include the range.</p>
<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>What is the most important Google AI Overview statistic in 2026?</strong></p>
<p>The 61% organic CTR decline measured by Seer Interactive is the most significant finding. It confirms that AI Overviews fundamentally reduce clicks to websites for queries where they appear. This single stat shapes every content strategy decision.</p>
<p><strong>How often do Google AI Overviews appear in search results?</strong></p>
<p>AI Overviews trigger on approximately 48% of all Google search queries as of March 2026. The rate varies by query type: 88% for healthcare, 83% for education, and 37% for entertainment. Informational queries trigger AI Overviews 39.4% of the time.</p>
<p><strong>Do AI Overviews help or hurt website traffic?</strong></p>
<p>Both. Overall, AI Overviews reduce organic CTR by 34-61%. But brands cited within AI Overviews earn 35% more organic clicks and 91% more paid clicks compared to uncited brands. The strategy shifts from ranking to getting cited. See our guide on <a href="/blog/get-cited-ai-search/">how to get cited in AI search</a>.</p>
<p><strong>How often are these statistics updated?</strong></p>
<p>We update this page quarterly. Last updated: April 2026. All statistics include their source and measurement date so you can verify currency.</p>
<p><strong>Where do these statistics come from?</strong></p>
<p>All statistics are sourced from published research by Ahrefs, Semrush, Seer Interactive, Search Engine Land, SparkToro, Advanced Web Ranking, and other authoritative SEO research organizations. Each stat includes a source citation with year.</p>
<p>The data is clear. AI Overviews are not a temporary experiment. They are the new default for nearly half of all Google searches. The businesses that adapt their SEO strategy to this reality will capture the traffic that remains. The ones that ignore it will watch their organic traffic decline quarter after quarter.</p>
<p><strong>Related research:</strong> Google AI Overviews are only one of five major AI search surfaces shaping traffic in 2026. For data on how the broader AI search landscape (ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, Gemini, Bing Copilot) cites and surfaces sources, see our companion analysis: <a href="/blog/ai-search-citation-statistics/">AI Search Citation Statistics 2026</a>.</p>
